-- Romania's Priority Is Fiscal Consolidation, President Basescu Tells FT
-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 2010-12-14T02:26:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/basescu-says-romania-focused-on-fiscal-consolidation-ft-says.html
Romania’s priority is to achieve
fiscal consolidation through a package of austerity measures and
further spending cuts that will come into effect in January,
Romanian President  Traian Basescu  said in an interview, the
Financial Times reported.  The country will have “slight” growth of 1.5 percent next
year, according to “the IMF’s evaluation, the EU’s evaluation
and our evaluation,” Basescu told the FT.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
